ghtered and waited proceeding orders for 9 days. Finally vessel traversed up river to KM 171 for more lightering to barges prior final discharge at berth in San Lorenzo. All STS costs were settled directly by charterers and port costs were capped at $75k in Argentina. Time awaiting orders depleted laytime quickly and ultimately we sent a demurrage claim for $600k USD."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-07-01T18:51:14.05","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Corrected Freight"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-06-26T15:01:15.857","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"dates/time updated with receipt of final discharge plans - demurrage estimate increased 10 days"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-06-21T16:53:59.023","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"KM 171 and San Lorenzo discharge added - Alpha Zone TSA and KM 171 to be charged via interim port?"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-06-17T15:36:25.08","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"vessel ordered to Alpha Zone to await orders / approve potential STS before upriver transit"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-06-04T12:06:50.417","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"voyage updated to reflect discharge in San Lorenzo - freight increased from $15/mt to $19.73/mt at WS 215 - max port cost Argy 75k"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}